value.snippet: Arkhangelskoye (Russian: Арха́нгельское, Bashkir: Архангел) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Arkhangelsky District of the Republic of Bashkortostan, Russia. Population: 5,819 (2010 Census); 5,641 (2002 Census); 5,387 (1989 Census). References Notes
